Hello, peeps! :wave:

I am sending data back from Airtable to a custom object in HubSpot via zapier (API).
I already made it happen using API Keys, but now I am trying to make it work using Access Tokens (OAuth), however, I am struggling to make my Javascript HTTP Request to work and get the token.

*This is my request:*
```var myTokenURL = "<https://api.hubapi.com/oauth/v1/token>";

var myTokenHeader = "Content-type:application/x-www-form-urlencoded;charset=utf-8";

var myTokenBody = {
    grant_type: "refresh_token",
    client_id: "xxxxx",
    client_secret: "xxxxx",
    refresh_token: "xxxxx"
};

var myRequestOptions = {
  method: "POST",
  headers: myTokenHeader,
  body: myTokenBody
};

var myToken = await fetch(myTokenURL, myRequestOptions)
  .then((response) =&gt; response.json())
  .then((json) =&gt; console.log(json))
  .catch(callback);

output = {myToken};```
This is the response:
```{
status: 'BAD_GRANT_TYPE',
message: 'missing or unknown grant type',
}```
If anyone has any idea of why I am getting such error response, I will really appreciate any help! :pray:
Thanks in advance :slightly_smiling_face:
